Updated Privacy Policy
Privacy Policy for LinkedIn Job Highlighter
Effective Date: 01/08/2025
________________________________________
Introduction
The LinkedIn Job Highlighter extension enhances your job search experience on LinkedIn by visually highlighting job statuses such as "Viewed," "Applied," and "Saved," and by enabling keyword-based highlights in job descriptions. Your privacy is important to us, and we are committed to being transparent about how this extension operates and handles user data.
________________________________________
Data Collection and Usage
1.	No Data Collection:
o	This extension does not collect, store, or transmit any personal or non-personal user data.
2.	Local Processing Only:
o	All functionality provided by the extension (e.g., highlighting job statuses or user-defined keywords) operates entirely within your browser.
o	No data is sent to external servers, third parties, or databases.
3.	No Tracking:
o	The extension does not monitor your activity on LinkedIn or any other websites.
________________________________________
Permissions
To function as intended, the extension requires the following permissions:
1.	activeTab:
o	Allows the extension to interact with the currently active LinkedIn job page.
o	This permission is only used to apply visual highlights based on job statuses and user-defined keywords.
2.	https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/*:
o	Restricts the extension’s functionality to LinkedIn job pages only.
Important: These permissions are strictly limited to the enhancement of your LinkedIn job search experience and are not used for any other purposes.
________________________________________
Third-Party Access
This extension:
•	Does not share, sell, or transfer user data to any third parties.
•	Operates independently and does not interact with any external entities.
________________________________________
Security
We prioritize your security:
1.	Client-Side Only:
o	All processes are executed locally within your browser.
o	No remote code or scripts are loaded or executed.
2.	No External Interaction:
o	The extension does not communicate with external servers, APIs, or databases.
________________________________________
Transparency and Consent
•	This extension does not collect any user data, so no user consent is required.
•	Permissions are used only to deliver the extension’s described functionality.
________________________________________
Changes to This Privacy Policy
This privacy policy may be updated periodically to reflect new features or changes in Chrome Web Store requirements. Updates will be published alongside the extension on the Chrome Web Store.
________________________________________
